<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF85635FFC2D76BFF9500E3" blockId="26.[121,750,1915,2027]" lastBlockId="26.[794,1422,1798,2027]" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FFC2D76BFCD100E2" bold="true" box="[121,186,1915,1939]" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FF72D76CFDEA00E2" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[201,385,1916,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FF72D76CFDEA00E2" box="[201,385,1916,1939]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">Bama monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of the genus in the non-compressed, distally almost finger-like medial prominence of the mid coxa. As in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FDEED7A6FE8E00BC" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[597,741,1974,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FDEED7A6FE8E00BC" box="[597,741,1974,1997]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this prominence has an isolated stout terminal setula. This last feature, together with many features of coloration, suggest a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FB7DD734F930004A" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1222,1371,1828,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FB7DD734F930004A" box="[1222,1371,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FCA1D751FFC60029" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[794,941,1857,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FCA1D751FFC60029" box="[794,941,1857,1880]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FB1FD751F95C0029" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1188,1335,1857,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FB1FD751F95C0029" box="[1188,1335,1857,1880]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very distinct from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FC46D74EF8E50004" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1021,1166,1886,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FC46D74EF8E50004" box="[1021,1166,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and similar in detail to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF85635FCD3D76CFF9C00E2" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[872,1015,1916,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF85635FCD3D76CFF9C00E2" box="[872,1015,1916,1939]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">B. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF85635FC83D788FFEF009B" blockId="26.[794,1422,1798,2027]" pageId="26" pageNumber="50">The specific epithet is a Latin participle, pointing out or indicating, in reference to the finger-like process on the mid coxa.</paragraph>
